"'''Starry Night Over the Rhône'''" is one of [[Vincent van Gogh]]'s paintings of Arles at night, painted on the bank of the Rhône that was only a minute or two's walk from the Yellow House on the Place Lamartine that Van Gogh was renting at the time.

The painting depicts the night sky over the river, with the gas lighting of the town reflected in the water and a couple strolling along the foreground bank. Painted in September 1888, it is held by the [[Musée d'Orsay]] in [[Paris]] and predates the more famous "The Starry Night" by nearly a year.
